snippet: Human rights advocates and even members of Daw Aung San Suu Kyi’s political party are raising questions about her performance in the broader political arena.
abstract: Political leader Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, while bringing about positive changes on local level in Myanmar since her release from prison, had disappointed those who expected staunch human rights advocate willing to tackle country's biggest issues.
lead_paragraph: Human rights advocates and even members of Daw Aung San Suu Kyi’s political party are raising questions about her performance in the broader political arena.

headline.main: For Some, Daw Aung San Suu Kyi Falls Short of Expectations in Myanmar
headline.print_headline: As Politician, Burmese Resistance Icon Disappoints Some
